The paper deals with lower bounds on the reliability function of a point-to-point discrete memoryless channel (DMC) and a two-user discrete memoryless (DM) multiple-access channel (MAC). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of random coding, typical random coding, and expurgated bound, which are common techniques in coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the constant composition code ensemble, which is a concept in statistical inference (cs.SI). The use of multiple access channels suggests that the paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories.
